Female.description: Rose-breasted Grosbeaks only overlap with Black-headed Grosbeaks in the Great Plains. Female Rose-breasted Grosbeaks tend to have more streaking on a whiter breast, whereas female Black-headed have an orange-buffy breast without streaking in the center. They also tend to have a whiter eyebrow.

Female/immature.description: Female/immature Blue Grosbeaks lack the bold stripes on the head that female Black-headed Grosbeaks have.

Adult male.description: Spotted Towhees have a considerably smaller bill and a longer tail than Black-headed Grosbeaks. The orange coloring is restrict to their sides unlike the fully orange belly on adult male Black-headed Grosbeaks.

Female (Red-winged).description: Female Red-winged Blackbirds have a longer and more pointed bill than Black-headed Grosbeaks. Females also have bold streaking over the entire breast that female/immature Black-headed do not have.

Adult male.description: Bullock’s Orioles are slimmer overall with a thinner bill than Black-headed Grosbeaks. Adult males are brighter orange than the more muted cinnamon-colored grosbeak.

Female/immature.description: Female/immature Cassin's Finches have considerably smaller bills, more uniform brown streaking throughout, less white in the wings, and lack the female Black-headed Grosbeak’s buffy breast.

Female/immature (Western).description: Female/immature Purple Finches have considerably smaller bills, more uniform brown streaking throughout, less white in the wings, and lack the female Black-headed Grosbeak’s buffy breast.
